    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.6111/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the Soviet
                        Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="68" xml:id="d484fn68">The translation of this telegram was sent on June
                        13, 1942, to Secretary of State Hull by Ambassador Litvinov. It was
                        transmitted to President Roosevelt on June 17.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-12">June 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Before returning to my country I allow myself once more to express to you, Mr.
                    President, the great satisfaction I feel in having reached a full understanding
                    concerning the urgent tasks connected with the creation of a second front in
                    Europe in 1942 for speeding up the rout of Hitlerite Germany, and concerning
                    co-operation of our countries in the post-war period in the interests of all
                    freedom-loving peoples.</p>
                <p>Please accept my sincere gratitude for the cordial reception and hospitality
                    offered to us by you, Mr. President, and the Government of the United States of
                    America, and my best wishes to you personally and to the people of the United
                    States of America.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vyacheslav Molotov</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
